subSubSection.paragraph:
The single species known in this genus (
Chant & McMurtry, 2005b
) was described from Africa. Distinguishing characteristics of this genus are: sum of the ratios “length of dorsal shield/ length of S4” and “length of dorsal shield/ length of S5” greater than 26.0; idiosomal setal pattern 10A:10B/JV-3:ZV (seta J1 present); r3 and R1 inserted on dorsal shield; absence of seta z6; seta s4 at least twice as long as one or more of the other lateral setae; setae z2 and z4 not longer than distances between their bases and bases of next setae behind.
